[thinking] I’m thinking about how MethodHandle invokeExact calls might be compiled directly. I wonder if the stack trace could show that the test isn't targeting properly. It seems like coverage through bytecode instrumentation should pick that up. Maybe the instrumentation only gets triggered when a private method is invoked reflectively, particularly by the serialization subsystem. It's a bit unclear how that all interacts, but I’ll keep exploring!
